        "original text": "V. Comparison of transcriptomic profiles between liposarcoma subtypes and control samples:\n\u2460 Focus on TODL lncRNA:\nWe focussed on a specific and novel lncRNA (TCONS_00064445) which we termed TODL, transcript overexpressed in dedifferentiated liposarcoma. The expression of TODL lncRNA was very high in dedifferentiated liposarcoma cells, comparable to levels noted in protein-coding genes (Supplemental Table ST2). TODL is in the amplicon of chromosome 12q15 [chr12: 69409275\u201369418806] containing two exons with a total size of 308 base pairs. Real-time qPCR analysis validated overexpression of TODL lncRNA exclusively in LPS141 and LP6 cells (dedifferentiated) relative to control cells (HAT and ASC52telo; Fig. 2A).",
